        "content": "\n`parse_posted_at`, `Job.key`, `Job.content_hash`, `Job.to_row` are load-bearing for `Store.diff`. A bug here silently breaks dedup (duplicate notifications or lost postings) rather than crashing — worth the most test weight per line.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `parse_posted_at`: empty string, `None`-ish, ms-epoch vs sec-epoch boundary (exactly `1_000_000_000_000`), negative epoch, ISO with `Z`, ISO with offset, ISO already tz-aware, garbage string, whitespace-only, Workday prose (`\"Posted 3 Days Ago\"` — currently falls through to `None`, not tested/asserted).\n- `Job.content_hash`: stability across runs (same inputs → same hash), sensitivity to each of title/location/url/department changing, insensitivity to `posted_at`/`salary_range` changing (deliberate — no test proves it).\n- `Job.key`: uniqueness/stability, collision resistance across sources with same external_id.\n- `to_row`: `raw` is dropped, `key`/`content_hash` are injected.\n\n```python\n",
